### Applications

**Text-guided avatar synthesis.** Inspired by recent works [25; 69; 67] on text-guided avatar generation, we leverage a pretrained vision-language encoder CLIP  to guide the generation process using the given text prompt. The text-guided avatar generation process involves randomly sampling a latent code \(\) and a control parameter \(p_{b}\) from the dataset, and optimizing \(\) by maximizing the CLIP similarities between the synthesized image and text prompt. As shown in Figure 5(a), the generated human avatars exhibit the text-specified attributes, _i.e._, hair and clothes adhere to the given text prompt (_e.g._, brown hair and red T-shirt). The generated avatar can be re-targeted by novel SMPL-X parameters, allowing for additional control and customization of the synthesis.

**Audio-driven animation.** The ability of XAGen to generate fully animatable human avatars with fine-grained control (Figure 1) opens up possibilities for audio-driven animation. The 3D avatars can be driven by arbitrary SMPL-X motion sequences generated by recent works such as  given audio inputs. Specifically, we sample an audio stream and SMPL-X sequence from TalkSHOW  and use it to animate the generated avatars. As shown in Figure 5(b), XAGen is able to synthesize temporally consistent video animations where the jaw poses of the avatars are synchronized with the audio stream (highlighted in red box). Additionally, the generated avatars are generalizable given novel body poses and hand gestures, allowing diverse and expressive animations.

